  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Actions defined during and architecture review or analysis are documented, assigned&amp;nbsp;and tracked in an &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/workproducts/uam_review_record_B5C8210C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_ON-wgPIOEdyIELoltz1wKA&quot;>Artifact: Architecture Review Record&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Review Record is managed by the assigned authority, which:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Updates the document as required based upon input from the people assigned to action items;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Notifies actionees of required input or work as needed;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Closes the ongoing management of the Review Record when all items have been closed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is made easier through automation. A repository of issues and actions could be used to automate these&#xD;
    management tasks, including notifications of actionees.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
